title: Tennis: Kaplan looks to win in possible final year
text:
Tennis: Kaplan looks to win in possible final year Mike Zacchio , mzacchio@lohud.com 7:44 p.m. EDT October 21, 2015 Suffern sophomore Sydney Kaplan advanced to the girls tennis section finals, giving her a chance to win what could be her final section title. Buy Photo Sydney Kaplan of Suffern returns a shot to Maranda Sears of Arlington during the 2015 Section 1 Girls Tennis Championships at Harrison High School Oct. 21, 2015. (Photo: Seth Harrison/The Journal News) Buy Photo Story Highlights Suffern's Syndey Kaplan will face John Jay's Anya Ivenitsky in the singles final. Mamaroneck’s Alison Zerbib and Katherine Orgielewicz will face Ursuline’s Vanessa Ciano and Laina Campos in the doubles final. All four doubles players are freshmen. 
HARRISON - Last year, Courtney Ollis and Sydney Kaplan chased a state tennis title together. This year, they’ll have to do it separately. Buy Photo Mizuki Shionya of Rye Neck returns a shot in a doubles match against Laina Campos and Vanessa Caino of Ursuline during the 2015 Section 1 Girls Tennis Championships at Harrison High School Oct. 21, 2015. Shionya was playing with Clemence Balzano.
